subSubSection.paragraph:
Terminalia (
Figs 63–65
) brownish. Cerci separated from each other and from epandrium, not extended anteriorly beyond tergite 8; mostly grey pruinescent, covered with dark mostly fine setulae, spinule-like setulae on inner face subapically; cercus slightly shorter than epandrium, subrectangular and truncate at apex (lateral view), with notch forming small projection slightly beyond middle dorsally; without pair of subepandrial lobes beneath. Epandrium subtriangular, mostly grey pruinescent, subshiny anteriorly, with numerous long black setae along lower margin. Hypandrium small, subtriangular (ventral view), narrowly sclerotized along margin; bare. Phallus (
Fig. 65
) well exposed; mostly slender, evenly expanded on basal part, gently sinuate near middle, short apical part extended beyond cerci. Ejaculatory apodeme not extended beyond basal curvature of phallus, with broad lateral wings and narrow vertical wing.
